# Example scoped override for a specialized subtree.
# Copy this file into a deeper directory as `AGENTS.override.md` only when that area
# truly needs different rules from the repo root.

## Example uses
- higher-risk infrastructure areas
- generated-code areas with special editing rules
- subtrees that need stricter review or verification rules

## Example scoped rules
- Treat this subtree as higher-risk than the repo default.
- Require an explicit review before broad dependency changes here.
- Keep changes smaller than usual and mention rollback steps.
